{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, experimentation and prototyping in AI benefit from this blend, allowing for iterative refinement and alignment with human needs and values.",
    "Prototyping in AI can be difficult because of the inherent unpredictability and complexity in AI's capabilities and outputs.",
    "HCD may help by applying userfocused approaches to manage these uncertainties.",
    "Moreover, involving end users directly in the design process ensures that AI solutions are tailored to real-world requirements, making the technology more accessible, usable, and effective.",
    "In summary, the HCD perspective can complement existing ethical and technical viewpoints in AI development, as it offers methodologies to create systems that balance technical robustness with socially responsible outcomes that benefit people and society at large."
  ]
}